The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, July 27: The countrys FDI inflows have improved 13 per cent to $4.2 billion in April-May against the previous two months, Ajay Shankar, secretary in the department of industrial policy and promotion, said. There has been a pick-up in fund inflows because of return of liquidity and strength in the global financial markets, he said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 27: Reliance Industries and its Canadian partner Niko Resources invested $5.98 billion in the oil and gas fields in the Krishna Godavari basin block D6, petroleum minister Murli Deora said. RIL-Niko plans to invest $8.8 billion to develop the Dhirubhai-1 and 3 fields.                             
	 Mumbai, July 27: The Securities and Exchange Board of India today said that purchase value of a cash transaction should not exceed the total value of mark-to-market losses and other margins, including value at risk and extreme loss.                             
	 New Delhi, July 27: Tax concessions, announced by finance minister Pranab Mukherjee, have given a boost to the new pension system with the number of subscribers rising to over 1,100 against 300 prior to the budget.                            
	 New York, July 27: Citigroup CEO Vikram Pandit has asserted that the bank will not retreat from the fast-growing Asian business. He hopes to continue with the banks expansion in India and China, he said.                                                                                                                           
